		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>Hotel Rwanda</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>In my opinion, this is a movie that everyone should watch at least once. It is a very graphic and moving depiction of the genocide during the 90s within Rwanda committed by the Hutus. I wouldnt allow a child to watch this movie unless they were at least 15 or 16 years-old.<br />
<br />
I can honestly say I haven't cried that during a movie for a very very long time.<br />
<br />
If you do take my advice and watch this movie, be prepared to cry and if you do not cry once during this movie, you need to re-examine yourself and look in the mirror.<br />
<br />
The sad thing about this movie, somewhere in the world. Genocide is being committed and the western world does nothing still after so many cases that pile up year after year.<br />
<br />
It makes you wish you were bad and deaf sometimes.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
